node.text: Skating with your friends in empty parking lots with some tunes has always FELT this way, but thanks to @discoasis it finally LOOKS this way. What we’ve been dreaming and feeling for years has been transformed into reality and I love it! ✨Our Pigeon’s Roller Skate Shop party was fantastic and I loved meeting so many skaters, what a perfect night ✨Can’t keep me off this dance floor, can’t keep me from having the best time and can’t keep me from being SO excited for our next Pigeon and friends Skater Exclusive night on Tue Aug 17th🌴Come skate DiscOasis with me, Ashley Imani, Keon, Kels McGriff and Coco at the South Coast Botanical Gardens 8/17 5-10pm with music from our fav DJ Wayne @djwayned10 🌴 Skater Exclusive parties all require a password to purchase tickets. This party’s password: SKATER

node.text: Oh yes I did grow grapevines in my front yard so that my baby and I can harvest them together and enjoy them while playing in the sunshine. So sweet and a just a lil sour…kinda like this kiddo! But for reals I do NOT have a green thumb so I’m stoked to have harvested artichokes, sunflower seeds, peas, oranges, tomatoes (that’s an easy one) and now grapes from my yard this summer 🌻🍇🍅🍊

node.text: I’m feeling so good and so GRATEFUL. Hard work, dedication and a solid team are what makes my world go round. From home life to the skate business, so much to be grateful for. Thank you to everyone who has supported me, my team, my businesses and my family throughout the years. From learning how to roller skate and derby through Santa Cruz Derby Girls in college, then becoming a middle school Science teacher in SouthEast LA, to starting and managing my own roller derby league Beach Cities Roller Derby, then leaving my teaching career to buy my skate shop, marrying my first employee Jacob and having our beautiful daughter Maple, opening and closing the San Pedro and Venice Beach skate shop, getting hit with a craziness of the pandemic as a small business, doing a full rebrand twice in 3 months to follow my own heart, starting a print and dye company to make affordable apparel for skaters, to helping create this amazing skate party going down THIS WEDNESDAY. And so much more. Thanks for all the support from everyone, I feel it and I’m taking all that energy and putting it to USE for our skate community. Definitely very exciting things on the horizon that I can’t wait to share with everyone because it’s for everyone. Stay tuned ;) and THANK YOU! 🥰
